article.headline: Old Dominion beats Gardner-Webb 58-46
article.story: ST. THOMAS, U.S. Virgin Islands -- Trey Freeman had 22 points and Old Dominion scored 10 straight in the final three minutes to beat Gardner-Webb 58-46 in the third-place game of the Paradise Jam tournament on Monday night. The Monarchs (4-1) led by four before Freeman made a jumper and two free throws to spark the late run. Old Dominion opened the second half with a 12-3 run, but Gardner-Webb (2-3) closed to 48-44 on Adonis Burbage's 3-pointer with 4:26 left. Freeman was 2 of 3 from 3-point range and Richard Ross added 12 points and seven rebounds for Old Dominion. Jerome Hill had 11 points and 12 rebounds and Burbage scored 10 with 3-of-6 3-point shooting. Tyler Strange entered the game averaging 14.3 points, but went scoreless on 0-for-11 shooting. Old Dominion held Gardner-Webb to 29.1 percent from the field.
